3 3. Knowingly permits a child to be present in a vehicle when
4 the person knows or should have known that the operator of the
5 vehicle is impaired by or is under the influence of alcohol or
6 another intoxicating substance; or
7 4. Is the driver, operator, or person in physical control of a
8 vehicle in violation of Section 11-902 of Title 47 of the Oklahoma
9 Statutes or impaired while transporting or having in the vehicle
10 such child or children.
11 However, it is an affirmative defense to this paragraph if the
12 person had a reasonable apprehension that any action to stop the
13 physical or sexual abuse or deny permission for the child to be in
14 the vehicle with an intoxicated person would result in substantial
15 bodily harm to the person or the child.
16 Nothing in this subsection shall prohibit the prosecution of a
17 person pursuant to the provisions of Section 11-902 or 11-904 of
18 Title 47 of the Oklahoma Statutes.
19 B. The provisions of this section shall not apply to any
20 parent, guardian or other person having custody or control of a
21 child for the sole reason that the parent, guardian or other person
22 in good faith selects and depends upon spiritual means or prayer for
23 the treatment or cure of disease or remedial care for such child.
24 This subsection shall in no way limit or modify the protections
